ABUJA – Mr. Isa Abdulmumin, has been appointed as the Acting Director of Corporate Communications Department of the Central Bank. He takes over from Osita Nwanisobi as head of the Corporate Communications Department following his (Nwanisobi’s) retirement from service on Friday. Abdulmumin, a deputy director, has been in the Corporate Communications Department of the CBN since he joined the bank. He is seen as a thoroughbred professional who enjoys the goodwill and cooperation of his colleagues in the department, bank, media and corporate society at large. Osita Nwanisobi took over from Isaac Okorafor in 2020, and before then, was a Special Assistant to the Deputy Governor, Financial System Stability (FSS), between 2009 and 2011.